  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA15-kiḷavi">itu varaivu nīṭṭittavaḻit tōḻi talaimakaṟkuc colli varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante asked for marriage, speaking to HIM when the marriage was delayed.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA15">
<l>            muḻaṅkutiraik koḻīiya mūri yekkar</l>
<l>            nuṇaṅkutuki ṉuṭakkam pōlak kaṇaṅkoḷa</l>
<l>            vūtai tūṟṟu muravunīrc cērppa</l>
<l>            pūvi ṉaṉṉa nalamputi tuṇṭu</l>
<l>            nīyuṇarn taṉaiyē yaṉmaiyiṉ yāmē </l>
<l>            nērpuṭai neñcan tāṅkat tāṅki</l>
<l>            mācil kaṟpiṉ maṭavōḷ kuḻavi</l>
<l>            pēey vāṅkak kaiviṭ ṭāṅkuc </l>
<l>            cēṇu memmoṭu vanta</l>
<l>            nāṇum viṭṭē malarkaviv vūrē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from the coast of the strong water,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the cold wind tosses about,</l>
<l rend="indent3">groupwise, like fine cloth waving [in the air],</l>
<l rend="indent3">the great dunes rich with thundering waves,</l>
<l rend="indent2">having newly eaten our flowerlike goodness,</l>
<l>you have perceived it:</l>
<l rend="indent2">– as for us, in [your] absence</l>
<l>we have let go of all shame,</l>
<l rend="indent4">that had come with us all this way<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">cēṇum</term>: -um is used here as an indefinite, that is, "all the distance".</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">like an inexperienced [woman] of spotless fidelity</l>
<l rend="indent2">lets go of [her] infant when an evil spirit drags [it away],<note place="foot">T.V.G. explains this as a human sacrifice. What, however, would be the context? And is it possible to find parallels?</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">enduring while [our] consenting heart endures.</l>
<l rend="indent3">May this village gossip.</l>
        
</lg>
         </div>
          </body>
